                    <td style={`padding:9px 14px; font-weight:600; ${n==='4'?'color:#f97316;':n==='1–3'?'color:#7c3aed;':'color:#374151;'}`}>{v}</td>
                    <td style="padding:9px 14px; color:#6b7280;">{d}</td>
                  </tr>
                ))}
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <div style="background:#fff8f0; border:1px solid #fed7aa; border-radius:8px; padding:14px 18px; margin:20px 0;">
            <p style="margin:0; font-size:0.87rem; color:#9a3412;"><strong>Important:</strong> The minimum passing grade in Albania is <strong>4 out of 10</strong> — applied at all levels including university. Our <a href="/" style="color:#f97316; font-weight:700;">ScaleGrades</a> tool is calibrated to this scale.</p>
          </div>

          <h2>Higher Education and the Bologna Process</h2>
          <p>Since joining the Bologna Process (2003), Albanian universities organize programs in three cycles:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Bachelor:</strong> 3 years, 180 ECTS credits</li>
            <li><strong>Master:</strong> 1–2 years, 60–120 ECTS credits</li>
            <li><strong>Doctorate:</strong> Minimum 3 years</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Albanian degrees are recognized in over 48 European countries. Students can participate in <strong>Erasmus+</strong>.</p>

          <h3>University Admission</h3>
          <p>Regulated by <strong>ASCAP</strong>. Students apply at <strong>u-albania.al</strong> and choose up to 10 program preferences.</p>

          <h3>Study Costs</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Public universities:</strong> €150 – €700/year</li>
            <li><strong>Private universities:</strong> €1,500 – €5,000/year</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Language of Instruction</h2>
          <p><strong>Albanian</strong> is the official language of instruction. Private universities like Epoka, UNYT and CIT offer programs 100% in <strong>English</strong>.</p>

